First, we need to find the symmetric difference of A and B (A △ B). The symmetric difference is the set of elements which are in either of the sets, but not in their intersection.

A = {1, 2, 3}
B = {2, 3, 4}

Intersection of A and B (A ∩ B) = {2, 3}

Now, we can find the symmetric difference (A △ B):

A △ B = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B) = {1, 2, 3, 4} - {2, 3} = {1, 4}

Now, we need to find the symmetric difference of (A △ B) and B:

(A △ B) = {1, 4}
B = {2, 3, 4}

Intersection of (A △ B) and B ((A △ B) ∩ B) = {4}

Now, we can find the symmetric difference ((A △ B) △ B):

(A △ B) △ B = ((A △ B) ∪ B) - ((A △ B) ∩ B) = {1, 2, 3, 4} - {4} = {1, 2, 3}

So, the symmetric difference of (A △ B) △ B is {1, 2, 3}.
